# Risk Engine Changes

## Files

- `apps/api/app/risk/rules.py` — `RiskRules` model
- `apps/api/app/risk/engine.py` — `RiskEngine` enforcement
- `apps/api/app/core/config.py` — `RISK_*` settings

## Rules

- `BLOCK` = hard stop (append to `RiskVerdict.blocks`). `CAUTION` = warn only (`warnings`).
- Never soften a block in the LLM layer or frontend copy.
- ML signals (`_ml_hybrid_warnings`, `_volatility_ml_warnings`) are warnings only.
- Defaults: 20% single-name, 30% tech, $250 max trade, $50 daily loss.
- Any new hard rule needs a unit test in `apps/api/tests/`.
- Any new user-facing rule needs a matching `docs/playbooks/` section — see `docs/POLICY-SYNC.md`.

## Do not

- Add prompt-only guardrails without code in `RiskEngine`.
- Move risk evaluation after LLM generation.
- Auto-approve trades that received `BLOCK`.
